explains: adj. 低水平的；低级别的

sentences.en: Low-level slash and burn farming doesn't harm rainforest.
sentences.cn: 低水平的刀耕火种不会损害雨林。

sentences.en: Solid low-level waste will be disposed of deep underground.
sentences.cn: 低放射性固体废物将被弃置在地下深处。

sentences.en: Some very low-level responses may rely on isolated words or short utterances to communicate ideas.
sentences.cn: 一些非常低层次的反应可能依赖于孤立的单词或简短的话语来表达思想。
